es derived from <i>andr-</i> ‘man, warrior’. In the New Testament this is the name of the first disciple to be called by Jesus. After the Resurrection,  St Andrew  preached in Asia Minor and Greece. He is traditionally believed to have been crucified at Patras in Achaia. He was one of the most popular saints of the Middle Ages and was adopted as the patron of Scotland, Russia, and Greece. It has long been among the most popular boys' names in the English-speaking world, especially in Scotland. Its popularity in England was further enhanced by its use as a British royal name for  Prince Andrew  (  b. 1960 ), the Duke of York."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Andrew de Lanherne was born in 1180. He married Miss de Dol about 1213, in Cornwall, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1230, at the age of 51."},"et":{"1180–Abt 1230":"1180–umbes 1230","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1215–1257":"1215–1257","1180–1230":"1180–1230","Abt 1230":"umbes 1230","1215":"1215","1257":"1257","about 1213":"umbes 1213","1230":"1230","Abt 1180":"umbes 1180","1180":"1180","about 1230":"umbes 1230","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Lanherne, Cornwall, England":"Lanherne, Cornwall, England"},"fi":{"1180–Abt 1230":"1180–noin 1230","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","1215–1257":"1215–1257","1180–1230":"1180–1230","Abt 1230":"noin 1230","1215":"1215","1257":"1257","about 1213":"noin 1213","1230":"1230","Abt 1180":"noin 1180","1180":"1180","about 1230":"noin 1230","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Lanherne, Cornwall, England":"Lanherne, Cornwall, England"},"fr":{"1180–Abt 1230":"1180–environ 1230","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","1215–1257":"1215–1257","1180–1230":"1180–1230","Abt 1230":"environ 1230","1215":"1215","1257":"1257","about 1213":"environ 1213","1230":"1230","Abt 1180":"environ 1180","1180":"1180","about 1230":"environ 1230","Cornwall, England":"Cornouailles, Angleterre","Lanherne, Cornwall, England":"Lanherne, Cornouailles, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Andre